title: Party
name: party
description: The Party Subject Area encompasses core information which is common to all Parties. A Party is defined as any Person or Organization who interacts with LPL in one or more roles and who has a Name and at least one method of contact information (such as Address, Phone, and/or Email). Party Roles for a Person include, but are not limited to, Advisor, Licensed Assistant, Non-Licensed Assistant, Investor, and Employee, etc. Party Roles for an Organization include, but are not limited to, Institution, RIA Firm, etc. A Party may play multiple roles as a Person or Organization, but a Party cannot be both a Person and an Organization. This subject area represents a single source of truth for a Party even in cases where multiple roles exist for the same Party, and/or when data is available from multiple sources and needs to be mastered.

attributes.name: Party End Date
attributes.definition: The Party End Date is the date on which a person or organization is no longer active in any role in LPL.

attributes.name: Party Start Date
attributes.definition: The Party Start Date is the date on which a person or organization is first known to LPL in any role.

attributes.name: Party Type Code
attributes.definition: The Party Type Code is a means to identify a specific party as either a person or an organization.

attributes.name: Party UID
attributes.definition: The Party UID is an identifier that is assigned to a person or an organization to uniquely identify them.

attributes.name: Taxpayer ID Number
attributes.definition: The Taxpayer Identification Number (TIN) is an identification number used by the Internal Revenue Service (IRS) in the administration of tax laws. A Social Security number (SSN) is issued by the Social Security Administration, whereas all other TINs are issued by the IRS.

attributes.name: Taxpayer ID Type Code
attributes.definition: The Taxpayer ID Type Code is a means to identify the specific type of taxpayer identification number associated with an individual person and/or organization.

attributes.name: City Name
attributes.definition: The City Name is the designator for a place name, a second level geopolitical area accepted by the specific postal authority, such as the United States Postal Service (USPS), where the first level geopolitical area is State Code, and may be associated with a Postal Code. The USPS designates one preferred place name for each ZIP Code.

attributes.name: Country Code
attributes.definition: The Country Code is a means to uniquely identify a country, a region that is identified as a distinct sovereign entity and geopolitical area. An ISO 3166 Alpha-2 code (“US”) will be utilized for the representation of a country code.

attributes.name: Delivery Line 1 Text
attributes.definition: The Delivery Line 1 Text is a group of attributes that consists of Primary Address Number, Pre-directional Code (optional), Street Name, Street Suffix Code, Post-directional Code (optional), Secondary Address Designator/Identifier Code (optional), Secondary Address Number (optional). Alternatively, the recipient may use a PO Box instead of these parts in certain contexts.

attributes.name: Delivery Line 2 Text
attributes.definition: The Address Line 2 Text is a group of attributes, as an overflow from Delivery Line 1 Text, that consists of Secondary Address Designator(s)/Identifier(s), Secondary Address Number(s). It's rarely used.

attributes.name: Party Address End Date
attributes.definition: The Party Address End Date is the date on which an Address of a certain Type is no longer associated with a Party.

attributes.name: Party Address Start Date
attributes.definition: The Party Address Start Date is the date on which an Address of a certain Type first became associated with a Party.

attributes.name: Party Address UID
attributes.definition: The Party Address UID is a surrogate key attribute that identifies an instance of an Address for a Party.

attributes.name: Postal Code
attributes.definition: The Postal Code is a series of letters, or digits, or both (sometimes including spaces and/or punctuation) that is associated with a geographical area or large institution that receives volumes of mail. It is utilized as part of an address to aid in the sorting of mail.

attributes.name: State Code
attributes.definition: The State Code is a means to identify a subnational entity by ISO 3166-2 part 2 code. It is an extension of the USPS State Code that represents one of the 50 U.S. States, 6 underlying areas (territories or commonwealths), District of Columbia, and 3 Military Army Post/Fleet Posts.

attributes.name: Address Type Code
attributes.definition: The Address Type Code is a means to identify the designated usage of an address that is associated with an individual person, person within an organization, or organization itself. Generally, an address is designated as Residential Address, Business Address, and Mailing Address.

attributes.name: Email Address Text
attributes.definition: The Email Address Text is a means to identify an individual electronic mailbox for the purpose of sending an electronic message from one electronic mailbox to another.

attributes.name: Email Type Code
attributes.definition: The Email Type Code identifies the designated usage of a specific Email address. Valid values are Personal, Business, etc.

attributes.name: Party Email End Date
attributes.definition: The Party Email End Date is the date on which an Email of a certain Type is no longer associated with a Party.

attributes.name: Party Email Start Date
attributes.definition: The Party Email Start Date is the date on which an Email of a certain Type first became associated with a Party.

attributes.name: Party Email UID
attributes.definition: The Party Email UID is a surrogate key attribute that identifies an instance of an Email for a Party.

attributes.name: Organization Name
attributes.definition: The Organization Name is a term indicating the name identity of an institution, firm, or other non-person entity.

attributes.name: Originating Domain Code
attributes.definition: The Originating Domain Code is the means to identify the source of the domain from which a Party record came. Valid values include Advisor or Investor.

attributes.name: Originating Domain End Date
attributes.definition: The Originating Domain End Date is the date on which a Party is no longer known to a given domain.

attributes.name: Originating Domain Start Date
attributes.definition: The Originating Domain Start Date is the date on which a Party is first known to a given domain.

attributes.name: Birth Date
attributes.definition: The Birth Date is the year, calendar month, and day upon which a person was born.

attributes.name: Death Date
attributes.definition: The Death Date is the year, calendar month, and day upon which a person died.

attributes.name: First Name
attributes.definition: The First Name is the given name or forename of a person that is used to distinguish one person from another in a group, family, or clan with the same surname.

attributes.name: Last Name
attributes.definition: The Last Name is the paternal surname given to a person in addition to a given name (forename) and an optional given middle name.

attributes.name: Middle Name
attributes.definition: The Middle Name is a letter or word that is a second given name to a person and is between the given name (forename) and the last name (surname).

attributes.name: Nickname
attributes.definition: The Nickname is an informal name or sobriquet that is used to replace a person’s legal name. Typically a shortened name or name commonly used to express affection, amusement, or character.

attributes.name: Prefix Name
attributes.definition: The Prefix Name is the honorific that is applied prior to a person’s given name for the purpose of respect of marriage, academic or designation typically used in written communications.

attributes.name: Suffix Name
attributes.definition: The Suffix Name is a generational title that is applied to the end of a person’s full name for the purpose of generational distinction when more than one person in a family, clan, or group has the same given name(s) and surname. Generally referred to as generational suffix which includes Sr., Jr., I, II, III, IV, etc.

attributes.name: Extension Number
attributes.definition: The Extension Number is a secondary unique sequence of numbers associated with a Business Phone Number for the purpose of reaching a specific individual within an organization.

attributes.name: Party Phone End Date
attributes.definition: The Party Phone End Date is the date on which a Phone of a certain Type is no longer associated with a Party.

attributes.name: Party Phone Start Date
attributes.definition: The Party Phone Start Date is the date on which a Phone of a certain Type first became associated with a Party.

attributes.name: Party Phone UID
attributes.definition: The Party Phone UID is a surrogate key attribute that identifies an instance of a Phone for a Party.

attributes.name: Phone Number
attributes.definition: The Phone Number is a unique sequence of numbers assigned (following the International Public Telecommunication Numbering Plan structure) to a Residential telephone line, a business telephone line, or mobile device for the purpose of telecommunications.

attributes.name: Phone Type Code
attributes.definition: The Phone Type Code identifies the designated usage of a phone number that is associated with a telephone line or telecommunications device of the beneficiary. Valid values: Beeper Number, Cellular Phone, Facsimile, Home Phone Number, Telephone, Work Phone Number, Business Phone.

attributes.definition: The Employment Status is the investor's employment status at the time of application for an account or service.

attributes.name: First Name
attributes.definition: The First Name is the given name or forename of a person.

attributes.name: Government ID Expiration Date
attributes.definition: The Expiration Date is the date on which the government ID expires.

attributes.name: Government ID Issue Country Code
attributes.definition: The Country Code is a means to uniquely identify a country, a region that is identified as a distinct sovereign entity and geopolitical area. An ISO 3166 Alpha-2 code ('US') will be utilized for the representation of a country code.

attributes.name: Government ID Issue Date
attributes.definition: The Issue Date is the date on which the government ID was issued to the individual or non-individual for the demographic record.

attributes.name: Government ID State Code
attributes.definition: The State Code is a means to identify a subnational entity by ISO 3166-2 part 2 code. It is an extension of the USPS State Code that represents one of the 50 U.S. States, 6 underlying areas (territories or commonwealths), District of Columbia, and 3 Military Army Post/Fleet Posts.

attributes.name: Government ID Verification Date
attributes.definition: The Verification Date is the date the identification was last verified.

attributes.name: Government ID Verified By
attributes.definition: (blank)

attributes.name: Industry Affiliation Address UID
attributes.definition: (blank)

attributes.name: Industry Affiliation Relationship
attributes.definition: The Relationship is the description of the affiliation the Investor and associated person.

attributes.name: Inside Investor Corporation Name
attributes.definition: The Corporation Name is the if the Investor qualifies as an 'insider', list the name of the company they work or hold a significant position in.

attributes.name: Investment Experience Annuities Years
attributes.definition: The Annuities Years is the number of years the investor party has investing with Annuities. (With LPL or without LPL). Value must be NULL or 1-100. (Zero is not allowed.)

attributes.name: Investment Experience Bonds Years
attributes.definition: The Bonds Years is the number of years the investor party has investing with Bonds. (With LPL or without LPL).

attributes.name: Investment Experience Equities Years
attributes.definition: The Equities Years is the number of years the investor party has investing with Equities. (With LPL or without LPL).

attributes.name: Investment Experience Margin Years
attributes.definition: The Margin Years is the number of years the investor party has investing with Margin. (With LPL or without LPL).

attributes.name: Investment Experience Mutual Funds Years
attributes.definition: The Mutual Funds Years is the number of years the investor party has investing with Mutual Funds. (With LPL or without LPL).

attributes.name: Investment Experience Options Years
attributes.definition: The Options Years is the number of years the investor party has investing with Options. (With LPL or without LPL).

attributes.name: Investment Experience Other Investment Explanation
attributes.definition: The Other Investment Explanation is the text explaining Other investment.

attributes.name: Investment Experience Other Investment Years
attributes.definition: The Other Investment Years is the number of years the investor party has investing with Other. (With LPL or without LPL).

attributes.name: Investment Experience Partnership Years
attributes.definition: The Partnership Years is the number of years the investor party has investing with Partnerships. (With LPL or without LPL).

attributes.name: Last Name
attributes.definition: The Last Name is the paternal surname given to a person in addition to a given name (forename) and an optional given middle name.

attributes.name: Liquid Net Worth Label
attributes.definition: The Liquid Net Worth Label is the estimated value of the client's liquid net worth. Liquid Net Worth is a person's Net Worth less real estate and retirement accounts. Typically captured as a range of values. Authoritative source is a code representing ranges of dollars.

attributes.name: Marital Status Code
attributes.definition: The Marital Status Code is the firm-defined code that identifies the marital status of Person Investor.

attributes.name: Middle Name
attributes.definition: The Middle Name is the a letter or word that is a second given name to a person and is between the given name (forename) and the last name (surname).

attributes.name: Net Worth Label
attributes.definition: The Net Worth Label is the estimated value of the client's total net worth. Typically captured as a range of values. Authoritative source is a code representing ranges of dollars.

attributes.name: Number of Dependents
attributes.definition: (blank)

attributes.name: OFAC Verification Indicator
attributes.definition: The OFAC Verification Indicator is the field indicates whether the individual has passed OFAC (Office of Foreign Asset Control) verification.

attributes.name: Preferred Name
attributes.definition: The Preferred Name is the name client prefers to be called.

attributes.name: Prefix Name
attributes.definition: The Prefix Name is the honorific that is applied prior to a person’s given name for the purpose of respect of marriage, academic or designation typically used in written communications. The following are the acceptable values for Person’s Name Title/Prefix: 1. Mr 2. Miss 3. Mrs 4. Ms 5. Mx 6. Dr 7. Hon

attributes.name: Primary Occupation Description
attributes.definition: The Primary Occupation Description is the client's Position or job title at employer selected from a list of LPL supplied values.

attributes.name: Prior Investment Experience Indicator
attributes.definition: The Prior Investment Experience Indicator is the indicates if the Investor has experience with various asset classes, represented in years.

attributes.name: Retired Indicator
attributes.definition: The Employment Status is the investor's employment status at the time of application for an account or service.

attributes.name: Secondary Occupation Description
attributes.definition: The Secondary Occupation Description is the second Occupation where applicable.

attributes.name: Sex Code
attributes.definition: The Sex Code is one of four codes specified in ISO/IEC 5218, which are: 0 = Not known; 1 = Male; 2 = Female; 9 = Not applicable. The standard specifies that its use may be referred to by the designator 'SEX'.

attributes.name: Source of Wealth Label
attributes.definition: The Source of Wealth Label is the source of Wealth, also known as 'Source of Funds'. This identifies the primary source of funds being invested by the client and whose value is selected from a company defined list of common sources. The category of 'Other' required an additional text description of the source. This is not the source of funds relating to retirement accounts.

attributes.name: Source of Wealth Other Description
attributes.definition: (blank)

attributes.name: Suffix Name
attributes.definition: The Suffix Name is the a generational title that is applied to the end of a person's full name for the purpose of generational distinction when more than one person in a family, clan or group has the same given name(s) and surname. Generally referred to as generational suffix which includes Sr., Jr., I, II, III, IV, etc

attributes.name: Suitability Add Date
attributes.definition: A Date is a calendar date that may be represented in the form of 'YYYY-MM-DD'. [YYYY] indicates a four-digit year, 0000 through 9999. [MM] indicates a two-digit month of the year, 01 through 12. [DD] indicates a two-digit day of that month, 01 through 31.

attributes.name: Tax Bracket Label
attributes.definition: The Tax Bracket Label is the firm-defined code that identifies the tax bracket for the investor.

attributes.name: Years Employed
attributes.definition: The Years Employed is the number of years the client has been employed with the current employer.

attributes.name: Government ID Number
attributes.definition: The Government ID Number is the government-issued identification number.

attributes.name: Government ID Type Code
attributes.definition: The Government ID Type Code identifies the type of Government ID for the provided identification number. Valid values are noted below: Social Security Number Federal Taxpayers Identification Number Canadian Social Insurance Number Non-resident Alien Number National ID Number Passport Number Three-digit Plan Number (PN)

attributes.name: Regulatory Type
attributes.definition: The Regulatory Type is the description of the regulatory body or requirement being associated with the Investor. Values to be stored may be like: 'OFAC', Persons of Interest, Politically Exposed Person, etc.

attributes.name: Regulatory Value
attributes.definition: The Regulatory Value is the alpha-numeric value provided by the regulatory body to be associated with the Investor.

attributes.name: Risk Review Indicator
attributes.definition: The indicator whether the account has been reviewed and poses a risk based upon review by your firm's compliance department.

attributes.name: Suspicious Activity Report Date
attributes.definition: The date on which a SAR (Suspicious Activity Report) was filed for the individual or non-individual for the demographic record.

attributes.name: Governing State Code
attributes.definition: The State Code is a means to identify a subnational entity by ISO 3166-2 part 2 code. It is an extension of the USPS State Code that represents one of the 50 U.S. States, 6 underlying areas (territories or commonwealths), District of Columbia, and 3 Military Army Post/Fleet Posts.

attributes.name: Trust Established By
attributes.definition: The name of the person who made the trust, also referred to as the Grantor.

attributes.name: Trust Established Date
attributes.definition: The Date the Trust was established.

attributes.name: Trust Revocable Indicator
attributes.definition: A value to differentiate various types of Trusts. Values may include Revocable, Irrevocable.

attributes.name: Trust Amendable by
attributes.definition: The name of the person who can amend the Trust.

attributes.name: Trust Amended Indicator
attributes.definition: A flag indicating if the trust has been amended.

attributes.name: Trust Revocable By
attributes.definition: The name of the person who can revoke the Trust.

attributes.name: City Name
attributes.definition: The designator for a place name, a second level geopolitical area accepted by the specific postal authority, such as the United States Postal Service (USPS), where the first level geopolitical area is State Code, and may be associated to a Postal Code. The USPS designates one preferred place name for each ZIP Code.

attributes.name: Country Code
attributes.definition: A means to uniquely identify a country, a region that is identified as a distinct sovereign entity and geopolitical area. An ISO 3166 Alpha-2 code (“US”) will be utilized for the representation of a country code.

attributes.name: Delivery Line 1 Text
attributes.definition: A group of attributes that consists of: Primary Address Number, Pre-directional Code (optional), Street Name, Street Suffix Code, Post-directional Code (optional), Secondary Address Designator/Identifier Code (optional), Secondary Address Number (optional). Alternatively, the recipient may use a PO Box instead of these parts in certain contexts.

attributes.name: Delivery Line 2 Text
attributes.definition: A group of attributes, as an overflow from Delivery Line 1 Text, that consists of: Secondary Address Designator(s)/Identifier(s), Secondary Address Number(s).

attributes.name: Email Address Text
attributes.definition: A means to identify an individual electronic mailbox for the purpose of sending an electronic message from one electronic mailbox to another.

attributes.name: Email Type Code
attributes.definition: Identifies the designated usage of a specific Email address. Valid values are Personal, Business, etc.

attributes.name: First Name
attributes.definition: The given name or forename of a person that is used to distinguish one person from another in a group, family, or clan with the same surname.

attributes.name: Last Name
attributes.definition: The paternal surname given to a person in addition to a given name (forename) and an optional given middle name.

attributes.name: Middle Name
attributes.definition: A letter or word that is a second given name to a person and is between the given name (forename) and the last name (surname).

attributes.name: Party Type Code
attributes.definition: A means to identify a specific party as either a person or an organization.

attributes.name: Phone Number
attributes.definition: A unique sequence of numbers assigned to a Residential telephone line, a business telephone line, or mobile device for the purpose of telecommunications.

attributes.name: Phone Type Code
attributes.definition: Identifies the designated usage of a phone number that is associated with a telephone line or telecommunications device of the beneficiary. Valid values: Beeper Number, Cellular Phone, Facsimile, Home Phone Number, Telephone, Work Phone Number, Business Phone.

attributes.name: Postal Code
attributes.definition: A series of letters, or digits, or both that is associated with a geographical area or large institution that receives volumes of mail and is utilized as part of an address to aid in the sorting of mail.

attributes.name: State Code
attributes.definition: A means to identify a subnational entity by ISO 3166-2 part 2 code. It is an extension of the USPS State Code that represents one of the 50 U.S. States, 6 underlying areas (territories or commonwealths), District of Columbia, and 3 Military Army Post/Fleet Posts.

attributes.name: Trusted Contact Decline Date
attributes.definition: The date on which a Trusted Contact declined.

attributes.name: Trusted Contact Party Address UID
attributes.definition: A surrogate key attribute identifying an instance of an Address for a Party who is a Trusted Contact.

attributes.name: Trusted Contact Party Email UID
attributes.definition: A surrogate key attribute identifying an instance of an Email for a Party who is a Trusted Contact.

attributes.name: Trusted Contact Party Phone UID
attributes.definition: A surrogate key attribute identifying an instance of a Phone for a Party who is a Trusted Contact.

attributes.name: Trusted Contact Party UID
attributes.definition: A surrogate key attribute identifying an instance of a Party who is a Trusted Contact.

attributes.name: Trusted Contact Relationship Label
attributes.definition: A means to identify how the Investor and the Trusted Contact know of each other.

attributes.name: US Foreign Indicator
attributes.definition: (blank)

attributes.name: Trusted Contact Address Type Code
attributes.definition: A means to identify the designated usage of an address that is associated with an individual person, person within an organization, or organization itself. Generally, an address is designated as Residential Address, Business Address, and Mailing Address.

title: Account

attributes.name: Registered Rep ID
attributes.definition: The Registered Rep ID is an identifier which is associated to one or more Financial Advisors (depending on the type of Rep ID).

attributes.definition: Identifies the type of beneficiary being maintained such as 'Primary', 'Contingent', 'Owner' and/or 'Successor Owner'.

attributes.name: Beneficiary Party Address UID

attributes.name: Beneficiary Party Email UID
attributes.definition: A surrogate key attribute which identifies an instance of an Email for a Party who is an Account Beneficiary.

attributes.name: Beneficiary Party UID
attributes.definition: A surrogate key attribute which identifies an instance of a Party who is an Account Beneficiary.

attributes.name: Beneficiary Percent

attributes.name: Beneficiary Phone UID
attributes.definition: A surrogate key attribute which identifies an instance of a Phone for a Party who is an Account Beneficiary.

attributes.name: Beneficiary Relationship Label

attributes.definition: The Revocable Indicator identifies if a trust beneficiary is a revocable trust. If so, this attribute would be set to 'Y'. If irrevocable, this would be set to 'N'.
